Name: fflags
Description: An alias of fcsr[4:0]. Can be accessed by FRFLAGS or FSFLAGS pseudoinstructions.

Name: frm
Description: An alias of fcsr[7:5]. Can be accessed by FRRM or FSRM pseudoinstructions.

Name: fcsr
Fields:
bit[31:8]: reserved, 
bit[7:5]: frm, 
bit[4:0]: fflags
Description: Can be accessed by FRCSR or FSCSR pseudoinstructions.
Risc-V Description: Floating-Point Control and Status Register (frm + fflags).

Name: vstart
Description:
Not available for L71.
Written by hardware on a trap on a vector instruction - vset(i)vl(i)
Note: Spec: RISC-V "V" Vector Extension

Name: vxsat
Description:
Not available for L71.
Should be reset by SW before use.
Note: Spec: RISC-V "V" Vector Extension

Name: vxrm
Description:
Not available for L71.
Should be reset by SW before use.
Note: Spec: RISC-V "V" Vector Extension

Name: vcsr
Description:
Not available for L71.
Should be reset by SW before use.
Note: Spec: RISC-V "V" Vector Extension

Name: sstatus
Fields: SD UXL MXR SUM XS FS VS SPP UBE SPIE SIE
Description:
The sstatus register is a subset of the mstatus register, but not a seperate register.
Reset value displayed is for A71/L71. It is 0 for L71.
Note: A subset of mstatus. Reading or writing any field in sstatus is equivalent to reading or writing the homonymous field in mstatus.

Name: sie
Description: The sie registers are subsets of the mie registers.
Note: Enables or disables all interrupts in supervisor mode

Name: stvec
Note: bit[1:0] = 0/1, bit[XLEN-1:2]: 4-byte aligned (define bit[4:2] reserved)

Name: senvcfg
Description: FIOM is checked for FENCE instructions.

Name: sscratch
Risc-V Description: Scratch register for supervisor trap handlers.

Name: scause
Description: WLRL field requires to check the write value against the supported value. Convert unsupported value to 0x2 for write.

Name: sip
Instruction Access:
SEIP: SRO
STIP: SRO
SSIP: SRW
Updated by (direct write, not via instru:
SEIP: External pin (set/clr) 
STIP: External pin (set/clr)
SSIP: External pin (set to 1)
Description: The sip registers are subsets of the mip registers.

Name: satp
Description: Selecting satp.MODE=Bare causes the other fields to read as zero
Note: Active in S-mode or U-mode. When SXLEN=32, MODE=Bare,SV32; when SXLEN=64, MODE=Bare,Sv39,Sv48,Sv57

Name: vstvec
Risc-V Description: Virtual supervisor trap handler base address.

Name: vstval
Risc-V Description: Virtual supervisor bad address or instruction.

Name: vsatp
Risc-V Description: Virtual supervisor address translation and protection.

Name: mstatus
Fields: SD MBE SBE SXL UXL TSR TW TVM MXR SUM MPRV XS FS MPP VS SPP MPIE UBE SPIE MIE SIE
Description:
Preset SXL[1:0] = UXL[1:0] = XLEN at build time.
Only little-endian are supported, so MBE is reset to 0.
mstatus.VS is implemented, regardless of whether Vector is implemented.
Risc-V Description: Machine status register, which keeps track of and controls the hart's current operating state.

Name: misa
Note:
* Fields:
** MXL[1:0] field:  encodes XLEN, i.e. 1: 32-bit, 2: 64-bit, 3: 128-bit
** Extensions[25:0] field (Refer to Table 3.2 in Risc-V Spec Vol2) 

* Reset: at reset, the Extensions field shall contain the maximal set of supported extensions, and I shall be selected over E if both are available.

Name: medeleg
Note: medeleg has a bit position allocated for every synchronous exception shown in Table 3.6 (Risc-V Spec Vol2), with the index of the bit position equal to the value returned in the mcause register.

Name: mideleg
Note: mideleg holds trap delegation bits for individual interrupts, with the layout of bits matching those in the mip register.

Name: mie
Fields: MEIE SEIE MTIE STIE MSIE SSIE

Name: mtvec
Note:
0-direct mode: all exceptions set pc to BASE.
1-vectored mode: asynchronous interrupts set pc to BASE+4xcause
bit[1:0] = 0/1, bit[XLEN-1:2]: 4-byte aligned (define bit[4:2] reserved)

Name: mcounteren
Note: When the CY, TM, IR, or HPMn bit in the mcounteren register is clear, attempts to read the cycle, time, instret, or hpmcountern register while executing in S-mode or U-mode will cause an illegal instruction exception.

Name: menvcfg
Fields: STCE PBMTE CBZE CBCFE CBIE FIOM

Name: mstatush
Risc-V Description: Additional machine status register, RV32 only.

Name: menvcfgh
Risc-V Description: Additional machine env. conf. register, RV32 only. Same as menvcfg[63:32]

Name: mcountinhibit
Note: It can be used to stop performance counters from incrementing to reduce energy consumption.

Name: mhpmevent<7-31>
Note: Tie off

Name: mscratch
Risc-V Description: Scratch register for machine trap handlers.
Note: Used to hold a pointer to a machine-mode hart-local context space and swapped with a user register upon entry to an M-mode trap handler

Name: mcause
Description: WLRL field requires to check the write value against the supported value. Convert unsupported value to 0x2 for write.

Name: mtval
Note:
* set to zero or other exception-specific value when a trap is taken
* Exceptions to write 'faulting virtual address' non-zero value to mtval
Breakpoint, address-misaligned, access-fault, page-fault

Name: mip
Fields: MEIP SEIP MTIP STIP MSIP SSIP
Updated by (direct write, not via instru:
MEIP/SEIP: External pin (set/clr) 
MTIP/STIP: External pin (set/clr)
MSIP/SSIP: External pin (set)
Description:
MEIP/SEIP: External pin (set/clr),  
MTIP/STIP: External pin (set/clr), 
MSIP/SSIP: External pin (set).

Name: pmpcfg1
Risc-V Description: Physical memory protection configuration, RV32 only.

Name: pmpcfg3
Risc-V Description: Physical memory protection configuration, RV32 only.

Name: pmpcfg5
Risc-V Description: Physical memory protection configuration, RV32 only.

Name: pmpcfg7
Risc-V Description: Physical memory protection configuration, RV32 only.

Name: pmpcfg9
Risc-V Description: Physical memory protection configuration, RV32 only.

Name: pmpcfg11
Risc-V Description: Physical memory protection configuration, RV32 only.

Name: pmpcfg13
Risc-V Description: Physical memory protection configuration, RV32 only.

Name: pmpcfg15
Risc-V Description: Physical memory protection configuration, RV32 only.

Name: pmpaddr<0-15>
Description:
If pmpcfgx.A = NAPOT, PMPADDRx[8:0] == 9'b1.   
If pmpcfgx.A = TOR,  PMPADDRx[9:0] == 10'b0.
Reset not needed in address registers.
Risc-V Description: Physical memory protection address register. Note: MMU only reads pmpaddr[36:10] = addr[38:12] to support maximum 39-bit physical address and 4KB alignment.

Name: pmpaddr<16-63>
Description: Reset not needed in address registers.

Name: htimedeltah
Risc-V Description: Upper 32 bits of htimedelta, HSXLEN=32 only.

Name: henvcfgh
Risc-V Description: Additional hypervisor env. conf. register, RV32 only.

Name: hgatp
Risc-V Description: Hypervisor guest address translation and protection.

Name: mseccfgh
Risc-V Description: Additional machine security conf. register, RV32 only.

Name: tdata1
Note: See Risc-V debug spec (External Debug extension v1.0.0-STABLE)

Name: tinfo
Description: Set bit[6] to indicate MCONTROL6 type (in tdata1) is supported.

Name: mcontext
Risc-V Description: Machine-mode context register. Alias for hcontext

Name: dcsr
Fields: debugver ebreak* stepie stopcount stoptime cause v mprven nmip step prv

Name: dpc
Description: bit[0] is always 0. Not available for L71.

Name: mcfgctrl
Fields:
bit[XLEN-1:26]: reserved,
bit[25:24]: DIS_DC* 
bit[23:18]: reserved ROZ,
bit[17:16]: DIS*, 
bit[15:7]: reserved ROZ, 
bit[6:0]: DIS*
Description:
Custom configuration control.

Reset value: 
DIS_LARGE_TLB_PAGE=1,
Others=0.

Name: mpwrctrl
Fields:
bit[XLEN-1:9]: ROZ,
bit[8]: FLUSH_DCACHE
bit[7:5]: ROZ
bit[4]: FLUSH_ICACHE
bit[3:1]: ROZ
bit[0]: STOPPED

Name: mcachestatus
Fields:
bit[XLEN-1:25]: reserved, 
bit[24:16]: in use, 
bit[15:10]: reserved, 
bit[9:0]: in use

Name: ml2cachectrl
Description:
Custom L2 cache control
Not available for L71

Name: mcycleh
Description:
Not available for A71/H71.
RW not controlled by mcounteren.
Risc-V Description: Upper 32 bits of mcycle, RV32 only.

Name: minstreth
Description:
Not available for A71/H71.
RW not controlled by mcounteren.
Risc-V Description: Upper 32 bits of minstret, RV32 only.

Name: mhpmcounter<3-6>h
Description:
Not available for A71/H71.
RW not controlled by mcounteren.
Risc-V Description: Upper 32 bits of mhpmcounter, RV32 only.

Name: mhpmcounter<7-31>h
Description:
Not available for A71/H71.
RW not controlled by mcounteren.
Risc-V Description: Upper 32 bits of mhpmcounter, RV32 only.

Name: cycle
Instruction Access: MODE==U? (scounteren.CY==1? URO: Reserved): MODE==S? (mcounteren.CY==1? SRO: Reserved): MRO
Description:
Shadow of CSR mcycle. 
Not a physical register.

Name: time
Description: Shadow of mtime, storing mtime value in the time register.
Note: mtime: 64-bit memory-maped machine time register

Name: instret
Instruction Access: MODE==U? (scounteren.IR==1? URO: Reserved): MODE==S? (mcounteren.IR==1? SRO: Reserved): MRO
Description:
Shadow of CSR minstret.
Not a physical register.

Name: hpmcounter<3-6>
Instruction Access: MODE==U? (scounteren.HPM<3-6>==1? URO: Reserved): MODE==S? (mcounteren.HPM<3-6>==1? SRO: Reserved): MRO
Description:
Shadow of CSR mhpmcounter<3-6>.
Not a physical register.

Name: vl
Description: Only updated by vset(i)vl(i), and the fault-only-first vector load instructions
Note: Spec: RISC-V "V" Vector Extension

Name: vtype
Fields: vill, vma, vta, vsew[2:0], and vlmul[2:0]
Note: Spec: RISC-V "V" Vector Extension. When the vill bit is set, the other XLEN-1 bits shall be zero.

Name: vlenb
Note: Spec: RISC-V "V" Vector Extension

Name: cycleh
Instruction Access: MODE==U? (scounteren.CY==1? URO: Reserved): MODE==S? (mcounteren.CY==1? SRO: Reserved): MRO
Description:
Not available for A71/H71.
Shadow of mcycleh.
Risc-V Description: Upper 32 bits of cycle, RV32 only.

Name: timeh
Instruction Access: MODE==U? (scounteren.TM==1? URO: Reserved): MODE==S? (mcounteren.TM==1? SRO: Reserved): MRO
Description:
Not available for A71/H71.
Shadow of mtime[63:32].
Risc-V Description: Upper 32 bits of time, RV32 only.

Name: instreth
Instruction Access: MODE==U? (scounteren.IR==1? URO: Reserved): MODE==S? (mcounteren.IR==1? SRO: Reserved): MRO
Description:
Not available for A71/H71.
Shadow of minstreth.
Risc-V Description: Upper 32 bits of instret, RV32 only.

Name: hpmcounter<3-6>h
Instruction Access: MODE==U? (scounteren.HPM<3-6>==1? URO: Reserved): MODE==S? (mcounteren.HPM<3-6>==1? SRO: Reserved): MRO
Description:
Not available for A71/H71.
Shadow of mhpmcounter<3-6>h.
Risc-V Description: Upper 32 bits of hpmcounter3, RV32 only.

Name: hpmcounter<7-31>h
Description:
Not available for A71/H71.
Shadow of mhpmcounter<7-31>h.
Risc-V Description: Upper 32 bits of hpmcounter3, RV32 only.

Name: mvendorid
Risc-V Description: Vendor ID providing the JEDEC manufacturer ID of the core.

Name: mimpid
Risc-V Description: Implementation ID providing a unique encoding of the version of the processor implementation

Name: mhartid
Description:
Preset value for build time, driven from input pins.
H/L71: XLEN-bit input
A71: (XLEN-2)-bit input, bit[1:0] are core number.
